                    P. Martyr:] Theſe garments are (per ſe 

                       〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                    ) of themſelues indifferent, and doe make no man either godly or vngodly, loc. com. fol. 1085. amico cuidam. I doe not holde the vſe of theſe garments to be pernicious, or in their nature contrary to Gods Word, but doe eſteeme this vſe of them (omnino 

                       〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                    ) altogether indifferent, ib. fol. 1088, Hooper. This difference of garments I thinke not fit to be vſed, howbeit if other things which are preſcribed vnto vs from Gods

Word, doe remaine entire, I hold ths vſe of theſe Veſtures neither impious, neither pernicious, (per ſe, aut ſuâ natur à) of themſelues, or in their nature. Ibid. fol. 1089. Hoopero.
